<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-356-578  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 356 578.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  April 16 1990 n586 p101(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Would you become an engineer again? (career opinion poll onengineering)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bellinger, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Electronic Engineering Times' Career Opinion Poll conducted on Mar5, 1990 asked engineers to rate their job satisfaction andreceived answers that ranged from very high satisfaction to verylow satisfaction.andP;  Sixty percent of the respondents were notsatisfied with their careers, would not pick engineering as acareer if they had the chance to do it over again and would notrecommend engineering as a career to their children.andP;  Primaryfactors that influenced responses includes respect, salary,stability and advancement possibility.andP;  No single factor wasdominant though respect received slightly more responses as afactor than other factors.andP;  Respondents indicated that engineeringis an eight to ten year career after which management becomes alikely lateral path.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Opinion PollEngineeringVocational EducationCareer Guidance.andO;Feature:   illustrationm graph.andO;Caption:   Various graphs representing opinion poll results. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>